description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Physiotherapist ( x1 WTE Band 5) &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen within MY Therapy service to recruit an experienced and highly motivated whole time equivalent Band 5 Physiotherapist. The successful candidate will work together with colleagues, partners, patients and their families/carers in providing rehabilitation in the community thereby preventing unnecessary admissions to hospital / residential settings whilst also facilitating discharge. MY Therapy also provide therapy to the Wakefield Intermediate Care unit providing rehabilitation to patients prior to discharge into the community. We also provide specialist neuro, cardiac and respiratory services to patients in the community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;MY Therapy service is a large MDT incorporating Occupational Therapists, Physiotherapists, Dieticians and support staff. The team will provide an opportunity to be involved in the integration of services to see the delivery of health and social services to Wakefield residents in line with providing ‘care closer to home’.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Community was rated as ‘Good’ when last inspected by the CQC and the successful candidate will instil the Trusts values and behaviours in ensuring quality services continue to be delivered and to strive for further improvement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return we will offer: -&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regular supervision&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A friendly and supportive environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An inclusive and thorough induction programme.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Annual appraisal&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commitment to learning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The full job description and KSF outline is attached.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
